Pakistan: mystery disease kills young girl
------------------------------------------
A young girl who was a student of the 10th class passed away due to a
mysterious disease at Zezdi village near Kushum Tehsil Mulkoh [in the
Northwest Frontier Province]. Some suspected it might possibly be bird flu.
Eyewitness disclosed to this correspondent that the young girl was
suffering from twitching (jerking) which later converted into bleeding from
her nose and mouth, and she expired a short while later. [The tentative
diagnosis of avian influenza could not be substantiated].
[byline: GH Farooqi]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This "mystery" death of the child in the Northwest Frontier Province might
be another case of CCHF. Abbottabod, the town referred to in the report
from Rawalpindi, is also located in the Northwest Frontier Province.
Rawalpindi, where the 35 year old woman in the 1st report was treated, is
located in northern Punjab, not far from the Northwest Frontier Province
border. - Mod.CP]
